different set of people.

00:34:47.370 --> 00:34:50.850
But again, you hope
you have enough of them

00:34:50.850 --> 00:34:55.170
and that the basic
assumptions are correct,

00:34:55.170 --> 00:34:59.230
that you can take these
kinds of statistics

00:34:59.230 --> 00:35:02.230
as representative of
what you would have seen

00:35:02.230 --> 00:35:04.180
if you could have
been able to continue

00:35:04.180 --> 00:35:05.950
to track the same people.

00:35:08.860 --> 00:35:12.672
Some people actually think
this is better than panel data,

00:35:12.672 --> 00:35:14.380
in the sense that you
don't have to worry

00:35:14.380 --> 00:35:16.600
about people dropping
out, and the data

00:35:16.600 --> 00:35:18.280
